reviews.text: I love everything about the store especially the frozen foods. They're healthy, easy to prepare and reasonably priced. During the work days, I pick something up with maybe a salad or a loaf of bread for an easy to prepare meal for my family. What's great is that there's a good selection of frozen ethnic foods! We're always trying something new. Meal times are exciting!

This is a great place to buy groceries. Some of the health food grocery stores have a terrible reputation about being overpriced and having a strange and rare selection. Trader Joe's has a beautiful basic medium roast coffee that's $5 a pound. You can buy wine there at a very reasonable price and you can buy by the case. The produce section is amazing and comparable with everyone else's prices. If you like cheese this is the one place in the city to go to. They have some beautiful rare cave aged Swiss cheese and it's really good. they have five kinds of cheese there that you might have trouble pronouncing their names. It's an amazing selection. And on a strange aesthetic side point some of the most handsome men in the city seem to work there all the time. It's easy on the eyes and very friendly.

I love Trader Joe's! I think it's more affordable than Whole Foods. I don't think there is nothing not to like about it. I bought a bunch of wine when I was there mostly for cooking. You can't beat the two buck chuck though it's not that anymore. Still the price is good.

I moved from NYC 5 months ago and my Trader Joe's experience has changed tremendously. When I go the staff is delightful. Whenever I can't find an item either they get it for me or when they run out they let me know what days the product might be coming in. I've been getting consistent wonderful customer service since I started coming to this location. you won't regret coming in.

Even though its extremely hard to find a decent supply chain for vegan organic food, they actually do a decent job at it! I find great deals on organic produce like bagged organic apples and potatoes when I'm there. Sometimes they're a bit bruised but I use them for juicing and for the price that is acceptable. Basically they just buy up unsaleable lots from other health food stores and resell them. Kind of an outlet mall for natural foods. One thing I disapprove of.. is there's an obnoxiously large liquor department taking up half the store. And everything being packaged does add an element of wastefulness, it would be nice to see a bulk bins section. The cashiers are above and beyond friendly and helpful though and the atmosphere and location of the store are both ideal. Overall they are one of the best options in town!

If you are looking for Indian food near monument circle in Indianapolis then this is the best place. Ambience is good. They serve traditional North Indian food with drinks. Not so crowded, spacious and easily accessible. Overall good experience with this restaurant.

Been eating my way around Indy 2yrs now and this is without question the BEST place around. 

Food: Unbeatable. Absolutely stellar.  Whether you're a carnivore, vegetarian, vegan or otherwise, there are delicious options for all.  

Staff: Their courtesy and friendliness is only outdone by their genuine interest in giving you an ideal dining experience.  

Price: Very fair.  

Highly recommend.
Had lunch there today with my office. First time there. We all had the buffet. All left stuffed. Lots of goodness on the buffet. Restaurant was very clean and staff extra friendly.

Oh my goodness this treasure is so worth getting out in the snow to dine inside! The lunch buffet was everything I needed! The only thing that could have made this meal better was parking, but they can't control the city meters. Definitely plan out parking when you come and give yourself time to enjoy the buffet. A lunch hour doesn't do it justice!

Not authentic Indian food. It is how majority of the "Indian" restaurants have become in America, trying to adjust their food according to the "American" crowds taste(sweet, not spicy and dull) and in the process they are no longer serving Indian food.

Owner has not taken any steps to make his food Indian. Infact the food has got more and more sugar added to it since my last review. You don't feel like eating dessert by end of the meal cause you are already high on sugar.

Nice and clean with sweet service. They lost a star from me because they took out the hot tub. This was a huge bummer for me since this is a ski town and there is nothing better than the hot tub after skiing all day. Also the breakfast doesn't provide a lot of gluten free and vegan options.

Stayed in a King and jacuzzi suite. Check-in took longer than usual and while standing in line the floors/ceilings must be super thin in addition to the guest staying above the main office being rude and stomping. I was worried I would have to deal with that for the night. Luckily we were given a room on the 3rd floor. The jacuzzi had a chip in it right where we were required to sit. The room had a good view and everything else went well. Overall would still recommend.

I’ve lived in Boone for about three years and stayed here for the first time tonight. The price was very reasonable and the service was outstanding! Kayla, the receptionist, was incredibly friendly while we booked our room. Love that it’s located near a couple local restaurants and a grocery store. Definitely recommend!
Clean room, friendly staff, great location. Thank you for your hospitality

We usually stay here when visiting App State. Nice, clean, close, with a helpful staff. Breakfast is decent.
The heart shaped tub in the room was hilarious! Wouldn't use it for fear off catching something!
